<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#00ff00">Originally posted by MKaath on 12-20-2001 10:23 PM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">Search is done now.

Features I have in the pipeline right now, these will be done before it goes live:


Removing items:
 You'll be able to cancel an auction if there aren't any bidders.

Bidding:
 Minumum bid must be at least 5% greater  than previous bid.  You cannot bid on your own item.  Yes, you can still have your alts shill, not sure what to do about that.  If you think someone is doing it, leave a comment to me to investigate or leave a feedback message on that user.

Bid notification:
 Will allow you to place a watch on an auction and receive tells with the latest bid if you are online.  If you are the owner of the auction then you will see who the bidder is.

Auction closing status:
 My idea is once the item is exchanged both users flag the auction as completed or if you didn't receive the item or payment.  If people fail to complete too many auctions they will be barred from buying or selling.  

Things I am thinking about:

Item Value:
  Right now it won't accept anything under QL50.  Mainly to keep people from filling it with trash.  I can also get the credit value as the game sees it, but that doesn't always give a good idea of the value.  Any ideas?  I suppose I can simply collect data as things sell.

Auto-bidding:
  Similar to EBay, you bid the most you'll pay and the bot will automatically bid the minimum amount when the bid changes.

Channel spam:
  If I can get a good idea of item value, I can have the bot send messages to the shopping channel as an auction is close to closing on a good item.  Will help add userbase as well as get people the best price.

Think that's about it for now.</TEXTAREA>
</td></tr>
